<Class name="CM_VehicleVisitRecord" id="ae3cc40d-3e4f-476c-a337-4ed1840b7cf3">
    <superclass name="CM_Object"/>
    <persistentAllowed/>
    <sharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassPersistentAllowed/>
    <subclassSharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <transientAllowed/>
    <text>This class records details of a visit to the terminal by a vehicle.
A collection of visit records is appended to each vehicle.
The purpose is to gather statistics of vehicle performance.

Data is:
timeIn: The date time that the vehicle was processed through the in gate
timeOut: The date time when the whole job was completed (ie all items serviced)
dwellTime: Time taken to service the vehicle. Up to a maximum of two hours
numTIsIn / Out: The number of items the vehicle brought in and out (parent items only)
transferAreaId: Identifies the Terminal Area in which the vehicle was serviced
vehicle: The vehicle used. Inverse of CM_Vehicle.visitRecords</text>
